HEADWORD: Yautia
<hw>Yau*ti"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name in the
Antilles.]</ety> <def>In Puerto Rico, any of several araceous plants or
their starchy edible roots, which are cooked and eaten like yams or
potatoes, as the taro.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

